==Production==
The film was produced by RR Movie Makers and has the caption ''Guns don<U+2019>t need agreements''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/5213-9.html|title=RR Movie Makers have registered the title as 'Business Man'|publisher=Ibnlive|accessdate=}}</ref> Although [[Shruti Hassan]] was considered for the female lead, [[Kajal Aggarwal]] was cast for the role.<ref>{{cite web|title=kajal in business man|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kajal-signs-mahesh-babu-s-business-man-news-news-lfsmpjcdfch.html|publisher=sify|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref> [[Shweta Bhardwaj]] was roped in to perform an [[item number]].<ref>{{cite web|title=special song|url=http://raaganews.com/?p=12695|publisher=raaganews|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref> 

The film was extensively shot in [[Mumbai]] and [[Goa]]. The Muhurat shot was pictured in August 2011 and the regular shooting commenced on 2 September 2011 at Shamshabad airport in Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/66794.html|publisher=IndiaGlitz|title=Mahesh's 'Businessman' shoot from September}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ragalahari.com/news/12468/mahesh-babus-the-businessman-in-regular-shooting.aspx|title=Mahesh Babu<U+2019>s The Businessman in regular shooting|publisher=ragalahari|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref> The second schedule began in [[Mumbai]] on September 18, where [[Mahesh Babu]] joined the crew.<ref>{{cite web|title=mahesh joins shoot|url=http://www.ragalahari.com/news/12631/the-businessman-to-release-on-jan-12th.aspx|publisher=ragalahari|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref> Filming was held for 74 days and completed on 10 December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=filming completed|url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/34436/tollywood/businessman-shot-wrapped-up-news-details|publisher=supergood}}</ref> 

Dubbing works were done in Shabdalaya Studios.<ref>{{cite web|title=Businessman dubbing is on |url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/businessman-dubbing-is-on.html|publisher=123telugu.com|accessdate=23 November 2011}}</ref>

==Release==
The release date was fixed as January 11, 2012 even before filming started. Later, the date was postponed to January 13 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=jan 11th|url=http://www.ragalahari.com/news/12809/the-businessman-now-on-jan-11th.aspx|publisher=ragalahari|accessdate=20 November 2011}}</ref> The film makers have released in 2000 theatres.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/2000march20/tbmin2000theaters.html|title=Businessman in 2000 theaters|publisher=idlebrain.com|accessdate=12 January, 2012}}</ref> ''Business Man'' was the first direct release in Paris and Japan, along with other overseas countries including [[USA]], [[Canada]], [[UK]], [[Dubai]], [[Singapore]], [[Australia]] and [[South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/usschedules/tbm2.html|title=Businessman releasing in Paris and Japan (first time a Telugu release)|publisher=idlebrain|accessdate=}}</ref> The film was also the first Telugu film to be released overseas with English [[subtitles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/album/listing/entertainment/stills-mahesh-babu-s-business-man-11087#/slide/3|title=Stills: Mahesh Babu's Business Man|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=}}</ref> The overseas rights were bagged by Hari Venkateshwara Pictures, while RR Movie makers retained the domestic distribution rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eenaducinema.com/news/mahesh-businessman-movie-audio-event-live-on-ntv-and-gemini/2131.html|title=Mahesh Businessman Movie Audio Event Live on NTV and Gemini|publisher=Eenaducinema.com|accessdate=December 17, 2011}}</ref> The overseas rights for the film were sold for {{INR}}5.4 crore, making it the highest buy over for any Telugu film in the overseas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Overseas Rights|url=http://www.teluguone.com/tmdb/news/Mahesh-Businessman-Overall-Rights-54cr-en-8299c1.html|publisher=teluguone|accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref> The movie was screened in nearly 120 theaters in USA.<ref>{{cite web|title=businessman release in USA|url=http://www.teluguone.com/tmdb/news/Businessman-US-Release-in-120-Theaters-en-10539c1.html|publisher=telugu one|accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref> In [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]], Business Man released in 92 screens, with [[Prasads IMAX]] having run 33 shows on the release day. It was speculated that the film distributor had violated the CBFC rules pertaining to the film title.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-12/hyderabad/31051716_1_cinematograph-act-cbfc-andhra-pradesh-film-chamber|title='Businessman' throws rules to the winds|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=april 18, 2012}}</ref> The satellite rights of the film were sold for {{INR}} 6.6 crores to Studio N.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/79334.html |title=Studio N buys Businessman satellite rights sold for Rs. 6.6 cr - Telugu Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-03-14 |accessdate=2012-08-04}}</ref>
===Critical reception===
''[[The Hindu]]'' commented that the movie is a Wholesome package and Pure entertainer quoting "[[Puri Jagannath]] has proved that he's still the director with Midas touch with his latest release (''Businessman'')".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/article2800156.ece|title=A cool escape from reality, literall|author=Suresh Krishnamoorthy|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=January 14, 2012|location=Chennai, India|date=14 January 2012}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave 3.5 stars out of 5, said "''Businessman'' is an unpretentious entertainer that manages to strike the right balance. It might not be a cinematic wonder but sure has enough in it to keep you interested till the end".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/movie-review/11475984.cms|title=Businessman: Movie Review|author=Suresh Kavirayan|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=Jan 14, 2012}}</ref> Another critic Sunita Chowdhary from ''[[The Hindu]]'' cited as "The ''Businessman'' has a mix of action, image, dialogue and montage but what makes it entertaining is that all the above quantities are inextricably bound and linked together at every level with an admirably tight script. It is a regular story but structurally, technically and content wise, the director makes no mistake.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2798529.ece|title=The Businessman: Back in form|author=Y. Sunita Chowdhary|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=January 14, 2012|location=Chennai, India|date=14 January 2012}}</ref> ''[[CNN-IBN]]'' rated 3/5 stars explains "''Businessman'' is a film for Mahesh Babu's fans. Watch the film for the actor's sheer screen presence and Jagannath's punchy dialogues".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/telugu-review-businessman-is-a-must-watch/221104-62-131.html|title=Telugu Review: 'Businessman' a must watch for punchy dialogues, Mahesh's superb acting|publisher=Ibnlive.com|accessdate=Jan 15, 2012}}</ref>

[[Oneindia.in]] gave a mixed review, adding "There is only one actor in the film who is everywhere <U+2013> it is none other than prince Mahesh Babu. It is a serious film and hence its appeal is very limited. The film may be liked by the fans of Mahesh Babu but for the general audiences it is just an average film".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/telugu/reviews/2012/businessman-movie-review-130112.html|title=Businessman <U+2013> Movie Review|publisher=Oneindia.in|accessdate=January 13, 2012}}</ref> [[Rediff]] which gave 2.5/5 says that "The film is in Puri's usual style <U+2013> slick and stylish. It's filled with loads of entertainment but without the comedians. There's no doubt that Puri Jagan has played to the gallery and kept the masses and Mahesh's image in mind while conceiving this film.".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-businessman-is-a-treat-for-mahesh-fans/20120113.htm|title=Review: Businessman is a treat for Mahesh's fans|publisher=Rediff|accessdate=January 13, 2012}}</ref>

[[Sify]] expressed that the film was " Strictly for Mahesh Babu fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/telugu/review.php?id=14988630&ctid=5&cid=2430|title=Businessman review: Watch it for Mahesh Babu`s sake|publisher=Sify|accessdate=}}</ref> ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'' stated "''Businessman'' is a typical Mahesh Babu film all the way, evoking laughs with comic one-liners and subtle expressions, and criticized the story of an orphan who takes to crime to avenge the death of his parents".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/movie-reviews/businessman-review-exaggerated-feel-mahesh-babu-fare-544|title=Businessman review: Exaggerated feel to Mahesh Babu fare|author=B.V.S Prakash|publisher=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|accessdate=Jan 14, 2012}}</ref> Fullhyderabad.com rated the film 7.5/10, and said that "Businessman is a Puri Jagannadh movie that mostly gets it right... The writer-director deftly combines the several forces of dialogue, edgy camera work, background score and energetic acting..."<ref>{{cite web|title=Businessman Review|url=http://www.fullhyderabad.com/profile/movies/4691/2/businessman-movie-review#tabs|publisher=fullhyderabad.com|author=Deepa Garimella|14 January 2012}}</ref>
===Box office===
The film had the largest opening for a Telugu film, and collected a share of {{INR}} 13.78 crores, and a gross of {{INR}} 18.73 crores, on the first day of its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/76731.html|title=Businessman's first day gross: Rs. 18,73,54,000|publisher=indiaglitz.com|accessdate=January 16, 2012}}</ref> The film has collected a share of {{INR}} 41.83 crores, and a gross of {{INR}} 62.93 crore in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telugu.way2movies.com/newssingle_telugu.html?id=179768&cat=4&tit=Mahesh%92s-Businessman-first-week-collections|title=Mahesh<U+2019>s Businessman first week collections|publisher=way2movies.com|accessdate=Jan 20, 2012 3:51 pm}}</ref> The film has completed 50 days in 350 centres.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/78812.html|title=Businessman completes 50 days in 350 centres|publisher=indiaglitz.com|accessdate=March 02, 2012}}</ref> The film has completed 100 days in 3 centres.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinejosh.com/telugu-news-gossip/20691/businessman-100-days-centers.html|title=Businessman 100 Days Centers|publisher=cinejosh.com|accessdate=Apr 14, 2012 10:01 PM}}</ref>
===Home Media===
The film was released by Universal Home Entertainment in the United States on a single disc [[HD DVD]] and [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]] on May 7, 2012 and in India on May 11, 2012 on a two disc [[Video CD|VCD]],a single disc [[Anamorphic widescreen]] [[DVD]] and also on a 1080p High Definition [[Blu-ray Disc]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MaheshBabu_FC/status/199708328341938177|title=Businessman vcd,dvd,blu-ray release dates for overseas and india|publisher=twitter.com/MaheshBabu_FC|accessdate=May 7, 2012 8:52PM}}</ref>

